                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Hand a: mediocre; hand b: fine and careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid scarlet, strong red)</seg>Hand b resembles
                        the hands in AADM-005, QDS-007, RQG-003.<date>Hand a: 19th century; hand b:
                           18th century (?).</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication"> Nomina sacra; name of the donors; groups of lines
                           on the incipit page of Text I-2; incipit of all other texts, incipit of
                           (sub)sections of texts and section numbers of Text I-2; first word of
                           each strophe of Texts I-3, II-2, II-6, II-7; elements of the punctuation
                           signs; elements of the text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.
                        </seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand a: <locus from="6r" to="14v">6r-14v</locus>; irregularly formed, right-sloping letters with short
                        hairlines.</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> Hand b: <locus from="15r" to="104v">15r-104v</locus>, 108r; neat and regular, with upright broadly spaced
                        letters. The quality changes significantly to the very end of Text II-7
                           (<locus target="#104r">104r-</locus>v).</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic"> ጵ has a modern shape, with the 6th
                        order marker set on the upper vertical line, directed to the
                        right.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <summary> The full-page miniatures, in the <term key="SecondGondarineStyle" ana="#SecondGondarineStyle">Second Gondarine Style</term>, were executed, or more likely painted, by
                        different artists, probably belonging to the same workshop. Those on <ref target="#d1 #d2"/> are much finer than the others and executed by the
                        same hand. That of the Crucifixion on <ref target="#d3"/> is more hastily
                        executed than the previous two, its shading is less delicate and its lines
                        less rounded. That on <ref target="#d4"/> also differs in several respects,
                        the background is monochrome and the artist has mistaken the outlining of
                        Takla Hāymānot's hair or turban for a halo: a mistake not made elsewhere and
                        a strong indication that he was following an underdrawing that was not his
                        own. Finally, in comparison with the others, the miniatures on <ref target="#d5"/> are crude and unsophisticated. </summary>

                     <decoNote type="drawing" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#3v"/>
                        <desc> An <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">More than 1 AT1012Equestrian</span></ref> miniature
                           showing <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">St George of Lydda</persName> slaying the <term key="dragon" ana="#dragon"/>. The saint thrusts his <term key="spear" ana="#spear"/> with a <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/>
                           finial in the neck of a dragon with a coiled tail, wings, and horns.
                              <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2790Birutawi">
                  
                  Birutawit
               </persName> looks at the killing from a tree
                           upon which she is perched. </desc>
                     </decoNote>

                     <decoNote type="drawing" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#4r"/>
                        <desc> A miniature of the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">More than 1 AT1031VirginAndChild</span></ref>, which follows the iconography of the
                              <term key="saluspopuli" ana="#saluspopuli"/>. <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> performs a
                              <term key="gestureblessing" ana="#gestureblessing"/> blessing gesture with his right and
                           holds a <term key="codex" ana="#codex"/> with his left hand. He and the <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> have rayed <term key="halo" ana="#halo">halos</term>.
                              <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7049Michael">
                   Michael</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4377Gabriel">Gabriel</persName>
                           stand behind the enthroned Jesus holding up a canopy. A <term key="donordepiction" ana="#donordepiction">donor</term> is prostrated beneath the Holy
                           Family. <q xml:lang="gez">
                              <supplied reason="omitted">ማርያም፡</supplied> ምስለ፡ ፍቁር፡ ወልዳ፡</q>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>

                     <decoNote type="drawing" xml:id="d3">
                        <locus target="#5r"/>
                        <desc> The <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1005Crucifixion"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">More than 1 AT1005Crucifixion</span></ref> miniature
                           features the <term key="deadjesus" ana="#deadjesus">Dead Jesus</term>. The <term key="bearded" ana="#bearded"/>
                           <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> is fastened by three nails to the Cross,
                           wears a loincloth, has a rayed <term key="halo" ana="#halo"/>, and has blood spurting
                           from multiple wounds, trickling down towards the skull of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1386Adam">
                  Adam
               </persName>. The <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">Virgin
                              Mary</persName>, to the left, and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5695John">John</persName>, to the right witness the scene. Both have tears
                           flowing down their cheeks, the former performs a <term key="gesturegrief" ana="#gesturegrief"/> and has a simple band <term key="halo" ana="#halo"/> the latter a gesture of
                           prayer and has no halo. The background is divided into two areas. The sky
                           above, occupies about 1/3 of the space and features clouds, stars, and
                           the <term key="sunandmoon" ana="#sunandmoon"/>. The lower portion does not feature any
                           elements. The miniature is inserted in a triple band frame decorated with
                           small triple dots at its upper and lower left corners. </desc>
                     </decoNote>

                     <decoNote type="drawing" xml:id="d4">
                        <locus target="#91r"/>
                        <desc> A <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">More than 1 AT1035HolyMan</span></ref> of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9162TaklaHa">Takla Hāymānot</persName> which follows the conventional iconography of
                           this subject and shows him in the <term key="gestureorans" ana="#gestureorans">orans
                              pose</term> with six wings and a missing leg. <q xml:lang="gez">ብፁዕ፡
                              ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ዘቆመ፡ በአሐቲ፡ እግሩ፡ ፯ዓመት።</q>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>

                     <decoNote type="drawing" xml:id="d5">
                        <locus from="108v" to="109r"/>
                        <desc> A two-page spread depicting the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1036MercyCovenant"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">More than 1 AT1036MercyCovenant</span></ref> showing two <term key="angel" ana="#angel">angels</term>, each holding a <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/>, next to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName>. </desc>
                     </decoNote>
